<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#9f9f5f"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Curious</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have heard reference to macro programs for AC but have not been able to find any.  Tried some for UOL but they did not seem to work.  Any pointers would be appreciated.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Raver[NaC]</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> MACRO!!! How dare you!! This is not UO and I seriously doubt a Marco would make the game any more enjoyable. The interface is so simple and intuitive WHY would you want one and to what purpose?? <BR> Here's the Simplest Macro of all if your having problems with the Key commands. PRINT THE KEYBOARD MAP AND TAPE IT TO YOUR MONITOR. Its that nifty little Word Doc they included with the game.<BR> Sorry if I sound like I'm flaming.. but I cannot stand the Idea of Macro's.. everybody always looking for an edge over the game. Play the game how it was designed... you'll enjoy it alot more.<P>Raver[NaC]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Muckraker</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I guess you mean play the game how YOU would enjoy the game.  Maybe that guy gets as much enjoyment from making a good macro as you get from clicking 1000000000 buttons.  To each his own, and no one appointed you the moderator of what people are allowed to do to have fun, thankfully.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Carhan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've heard Keyboard express works well, though it is not affiliated with AC at all</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD